<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="608" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[113,1089,219,692]" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,223,284,308]" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">Remarks.</emphasis>
Because of unavailability of the 
<typeStatus box="[560,608,284,308]" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">type</typeStatus>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Semenov" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[617,807,285,308]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grombczewskii">
<emphasis box="[617,807,285,308]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">M. grombczewskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was listed in ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hentz" authorityYear="1830" box="[953,1089,285,308]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[953,1089,285,308]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">Macrosiagon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- nomina dubia’ in 
<bibRefCitation author="BATELKA J." box="[310,493,316,340]" pageId="21" pageNumber="608" pagination="73 - 78" refId="ref27428" refString="BATELKA J. 2008 a: Family Ripiphoridae Gemminger &amp; Harold, 1870. Pp. 29, 73 - 78. In: LOBL I. &amp; SMETANA A. (eds.): Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Volume 5. Tenebrionoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 670 pp." type="book chapter" year="2008">BATELKA (2008a)</bibRefCitation>
. Thanks to detailed images of the 
<typeStatus box="[853,899,316,340]" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">type</typeStatus>
taken by Michael Engel (
<collectingRegion box="[190,270,348,372]" country="United States of America" name="Kansas" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">Kansas</collectingRegion>
) I am now able to offer several remarks regarding the systematic placement and validity of this peculiar taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[113,1089,219,692]" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Semenov" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[144,449,413,436]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grombczewskii">
<emphasis box="[144,449,413,436]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">Macrosiagon grombczewskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Marseul" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[610,751,412,436]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis box="[610,632,413,436]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[646,751,413,436]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">bifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group as it is defined in this paper. MT 2 is shortened and robust, flattened dorsally as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[781,928,445,468]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctata">
<emphasis box="[781,928,445,468]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">M. bipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the medial lobe of the pronotal disc is smooth and without an elevation. An identical combination of both characters also occurs in the African 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fahraeus" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[548,646,509,532]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caffra">
<emphasis box="[548,646,509,532]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">M. caffra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which belongs to the same species group. Males and more females of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Semenov" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[411,604,541,564]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grombczewskii">
<emphasis box="[411,604,541,564]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">M. grombczewskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are needed to prove the stability of these and other putative specific characters (e.g. carina and black spots on the pronotal disc) mentioned both by 
<bibRefCitation author="SEMENOV A." box="[203,377,604,628]" pageId="21" pageNumber="608" pagination="262 - 382" refId="ref30647" refString="SEMENOV A. 1891: Diagnoses Coleopterorum novorum ex Asia Centrali et Orientali. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae 25: 262 - 382." type="journal article" year="1891">SEMENOV (1891)</bibRefCitation>
and YABLOKOV- KHNZORYAN (1976). Until then I prefer to consider 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Semenov" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[113,307,637,660]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="608" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grombczewskii">
<emphasis box="[113,307,637,660]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="608">M. grombczewskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[113,997,667,692]" pageId="21" pageNumber="608" type="distribution">
